<subSubSection box="[199,1363,1537,1564]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,566,1564]" box="[199,1363,1537,1564]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1537,1563]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[853,909,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">sinu-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[964,1023,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">costa</emphasis>
, referring to the sinuate costa.
</paragraph>
